  <div id="description" class="container">
    <p id="descriptionTitle"><strong>SPOT GUIDE FOR CAPE KIWANA</strong></p>
    <p><img src="../img/surfboard.png" width="20px"><strong>Accessibility:</strong>  You can literally drive your vehicle on the beach. Parking fills up before noon on a nice weekend and the beach is sprawling with pickup trucks and Dorry boats launching directly onto the sand near the cape.</p>
    <p><img src="../img/surfboard.png" width="20px"><strong>Vibe:</strong>  Some localism exists. A beginner can expect to be dropped in upon on a crowded day.</p>
    <p><img src="../img/surfboard.png" width="20px"><strong>Crowd Factor:</strong>  Medium level crowds, can get busy.</p>
    <p><img src="../img/surfboard.png" width="20px"><strong>Skill Level:</strong> Although a beach break, this spot is best for intermediate level surfers and beyond. Often a dredging shorebreak style wave can be found south from the cape, whereas a reef-pointbreak works on a big swell next to the cape.</p>
